Platform: GPL9815(MIT-HRH-Celegans-MAS8. Microarray probes were oligonucleotides with sequences complementary to microRNAs and other small RNAs. Each probe was modified with a free amino group linked to its 5' terminus through a 6-carbon spacer (IDT) and was printed onto amine-binding slides (CodeLink, Amersham Biosciences). Printing and hybridization were done using the protocols from the slide manufacturer with the following modifications: the oligonucleotide concentration for printing was 20 uM in 150 mM sodium phosphate pH 8.5, and hybridization was at 50 degrees centigrade for 6h.)
